The paper discusses the optimization of hardware implementation of deep convolutional neural networks, which falls under the computer science sub-categories of cs.AR (Hardware Architecture), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also mentions the consideration of power and energy constraints, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.ET (Embedded Systems).
